snippet: A small passenger airplane crashed into a river in Taipei after clipping a bridge on Wednesday morning, Taiwan’s Central News Agency reported, citing a local government official.
abstract: Small TransAsia Airways turboprop plane crashes into river in Taipei, Taiwan, after hitting bridge; about 12 people are rescued, with 10 still trapped.
lead_paragraph: A small passenger airplane crashed into a river in Taipei after clipping a bridge on Wednesday morning, Taiwan’s Central News Agency reported, citing a local government official.
